        %p Chicago Ideas Week wants to provide extraordinary opportunities to extraordinary people. To accomplish this, CIW has developed Programs and Awards of Distinction for students, educators, and community leaders to develop, learn, and collaborate as participants of Chicago Ideas Week.
        
        %h2 ThinkChicago
        %p 
          ThinkChicago offers a unique and unparalleled opportunity for top-performing students from regional universities to visit some of Chicago's leading tech and startup companies. On October 11-12, 2012, 100 selected students in junior or senior standing will network with industry leaders, explore business headquarters in Chicago's booming tech scene, learn about exciting job opportunities, and gain free admission to the second annual Chicago Ideas Week. ThinkChicago is sponsored by the City of Chicago and the University of Illinois.
          = link_to "Read More", thinkchicago_path, :rel => "bookmark", :title => "ThinkChicago"
        
        %h2 Bluhm/Helfand Social Innovation Fellowship
        %p 
          The Fellowship program hosts three young social entrepreneurs in Chicago for Chicago Ideas Week, all expenses paid, for the purposes of gaining exposure for their organization, intimate meetings with nationally recognized business and community leaders, and funding to help advance the Fellows' social mission and goals.
          = link_to "Read More", blum_helfand_path, :rel => "bookmark", :title => "View the Bluhm/Helfand Innovation Fellowship Winners from 2011"

        

